  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Axian Telecom Bond</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Axian Telecom (the HoldCo or the Company), has invited IFC to act as anchor investor in its first ever bond issuance (alongside other DFIs), to encourage the market at a time when market volatility has been high and liquidity is tight, for an amount of up to US$420 million. (the Bond Issuance).</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The use of proceeds for refinancing in Togo seeks to unlock a capital expenditure program. The refinancing operation in Tanzania will also unlock investment that will result in increased access to quality mobile connectivity for individuals and businesses in Tanzania, a country with large connectivity gaps.</narrative>
  </description>
